  <span id="freeText3747830038797899750" style="display:none">This is a story of a bright gender non conforming, bright, autistic, genuine person named Sasha. This is also a story of a African-American, silly and also bright, but slightly more troubled boy named Richard. The first in a skirt, the second with a lighter, and the story that brought them up to a crime, five seconds that burnt up as quick as a flame(literally and figuratively speaking) that would change both of their lives forever, and the complicated but hopeful aftermath. Might I also add this is also very much a true story? This is a book for everyone,covers so many topics and does justice to both Sasha and Richard's side of the events beautifully. Something I highly recommend!!</span>
